    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-chilli-chicken-stir-fry-with-sesame-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into large bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-chilli-chicken-stir-fry-with-sesame-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-chilli-chicken-stir-fry-with-sesame-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add your <strong>chicken breast strips</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until browned all over</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-chilli-chicken-stir-fry-with-sesame-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once browned, add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong>,<strong> chopped pepper</strong> and your <strong>sweet pea pods </strong>and cook for 2-3 min further</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-chilli-chicken-stir-fry-with-sesame-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>cornflour</strong> with 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[225ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> in a small bowl</p><p>Add your <strong>red</strong> <strong>chilli relish</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong> and <strong>cornflour mix</strong> to the pan and cook for 4-5 min or until the sauce has thickened and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>sweet chilli chicken stir-fry</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-chilli-chicken-stir-fry-with-sesame-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once done, stir your <strong>black sesame seeds</strong> through the<strong> cooked rice</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>sesame rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-chilli-chicken-stir-fry-with-sesame-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sweet chilli chicken stir-fry</strong> over the <strong>sesame rice</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
